    store: Fold BatchCopy into TableState With recent changes, BatchCopy has become unnecessary

    by lutter

    store: Count entities during copying We used to count entities after all the data had been copied, but that is a very slow operation for large subgraphs; that in turn can lead to bad side-effects like connection timeouts and the copy ultimately failing. We now keep track of the number of current entity versions that we copy with each batch and calculate the entity count incrementally

    by lutter

    store: Clear the entity count when truncating a deployment We used to count entities, but we know the result is 0 because all the tables we are counting are empty

    by lutter

    by lutter

    store: Do not return a StoreEvent from Layout.truncate_tables
